article.description: Dominique Johnson tied a career-high 21 points to help North Texas extend its home winning streak to 17 games with an 83-64 win over Arkansas State.
article.headline: North Texas extends home winning streak to 17
article.linkText: North Texas extends home winning streak to 17
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Dominique Johnson tied a career-high 21 points to help North Texas extend its home winning streak to 17 games with an 83-64 victory over Arkansas State on Saturday night. The Mean Green (16-4, 5-2 Sun Belt) began the game with a 9-0 run and never looked back. They led 46-24 at halftime after Johnson hit a 35-foot shot at the buzzer. Johnson shot 5 for 5 from 3-point range and 7 for 8 from the field. Rashad Allison scored 12 points to lead the Red Wolves (10-12, 4-4) while Malcoln Kirkland added 10. George Odufuwa scored 14 points and tied his season-high of 16 rebounds for North Texas. Tristan Thompson added 16 points and Josh White 15 points for the Mean Green.
